com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.trusted_clusters.attestation

Interface Services

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Service, ServicesTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ServicesStub

    public interface Services
extends Service, ServicesTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Services interface manages the Attestation Service instances a Trusted Cluster is configured to use. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

    • Method Detail

      • list

        Services.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String cluster)
        Returns the basic information about all configured Attestation Service instances used by this cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        Basic information about all configured Attestation Service instances used by this cluster.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if the cluster ID is invalid.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires TrustedAdmin.ReadTrustedHosts.
        • The resource ClusterComputeResource referenced by the parameter cluster requires System.View.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        Returns:
        instance of Services.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • get

        Services.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String cluster,
                           java.lang.String service)
        Returns detailed information about the given registered Attestation Service instance that is configured for the given cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        Detailed information about the specified Attestation Service configured for the given cluster.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if the cluster or the service ID is invalid.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires TrustedAdmin.ReadTrustedHosts.
        • The resource ClusterComputeResource referenced by the parameter cluster requires System.View.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        service - The ID of the service. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.attestation.Service.
        Returns:
        instance of Services.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • create

        Services.CreateInvocation create(java.lang.String cluster,
                                 ServicesTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Configures the cluster to use a the given registered Attestation Service. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        ID of the configured Attestation Service instance. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.attestation.Service.

        Operation Errors:
        AlreadyExists - if the Attestation Service is already configured for this cluster
        Error - for any other error.
        InvalidArgument - if the CreateSpec is not valid.
        NotFound - if the cluster ID is not valid.
        UnableToAllocateResource - if all the hosts in the cluster do not have VMware vSphere Trust Authority enabled license.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - Describes the registered instance of the Attestation Service
        Returns:
        instance of Services.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • delete

        Services.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String cluster,
                                 java.lang.String service)
        Removes the Attestation Service instance from the configuration of the given cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if the Attestation Service instance or the cluster are not found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - the unique ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        service - the registered Attestation Service instance unique identifier. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.attestation.Service.
        Returns:
        instance of Services.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
